-- frames 4-7: task-decomposer-1 through task-decomposer-4
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- --- frame 4: task-decomposer-1 (SG1: core invoicing app) ---

⊢ task-decomposer-1
  given sub-goal ≡ "SG1: Build the core invoicing application (create, send, track invoices; manage clients; dashboard)"
  yield tasks[], rationale

  ∴ Decompose into 3-5 concrete tasks...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield tasks ≡ [
    "T1.1: Design and implement data models (Invoice, Client, LineItem, PaymentStatus) and database schema",
    "T1.2: Build invoice CRUD API (create, read, update, delete, send via email, mark as paid)",
    "T1.3: Build client management (add/edit/archive clients, contact info, invoice history)",
    "T1.4: Build dashboard UI (outstanding invoices, overdue alerts, revenue summary, recent activity)"
  ]
  yield rationale ≡ "4 tasks: data layer → API → client mgmt → dashboard. Ordered by dependency: T1.1 first (schema), T1.2/T1.3 parallel (both need schema), T1.4 last (needs API)."

  ⊨ 3 ≤ length(tasks) ≤ 5 → ✓ (4)
  ⊨ tasks are non-overlapping → ✓
  ⊨ each task achievable within timeline → ✓ (~1-2 weeks each)

-- --- frame 5: task-decomposer-2 (SG2: infrastructure) ---

⊢ task-decomposer-2
  given sub-goal ≡ "SG2: Set up infrastructure and operations (hosting, CI/CD, monitoring, security, backups)"
  yield tasks[], rationale

  yield tasks ≡ [
    "T2.1: Provision cloud infrastructure (VPC, database, application servers, DNS, SSL)",
    "T2.2: Set up CI/CD pipeline (automated tests, staging deployment, production deployment)",
    "T2.3: Implement monitoring and alerting (uptime, error rates, latency, disk/memory alerts)",
    "T2.4: Configure security and backups (database backups, encryption at rest, auth/authz, WAF)"
  ]
  yield rationale ≡ "4 tasks: foundation → automation → observability → protection. T2.1 first, T2.2-T2.4 can partially parallel."

  ⊨ 3 ≤ length(tasks) ≤ 5 → ✓ (4)

-- --- frame 6: task-decomposer-3 (SG3: billing and payments) ---

